      "severity": "info",
      "actionable": false,
      "suggestion": null
    },
    {
      "category": "a2a",
      "claim": "The use of RFC 7033 (webfinger) is a less common but potentially useful addition for agent discovery, though its adoption is limited. Its value depends on the broader ecosystem supporting webfinger.",
      "severity": "low",
      "actionable": false,
      "suggestion": null
    }
  ],
  "summary": "The Human Rights Observatory demonstrates a strong foundation for agent discoverability and interoperability through its implementation of .well-known files and a detailed agent card. Addressing the lack of cost information and proposal format documentation would further enhance its A2A capabilities."
